# Proposal Writer — CivicQ Landing Page

Wrote the three proposal deliverables into `upwork-runs/civicq/proposal/`,
styled with the demo's bespoke civic-tech dark design system (near-black
`#0B0E11`, teal `#3DBFA8` accent, muted gold `#C9A227` secondary, Newsreader +
Inter), not michaelwegter.com's palette.

## Files written

- `proposal/cover-letter.md` — In Michael's voice per `reference/brand-voice.md`.
  Leads with the live demo link (portfolio ask answered in the first line, since
  the posting explicitly disqualifies proposals without one), then covers: what
  was built (all 10 sections + /methodology, sticky nav, status pills), the three
  coded data visualizations (graphics-approach ask, answered explicitly: built by
  Michael, no designer assets), the working email-capture-to-CSV backend, the
  3-milestone timeline inside the client's 2-4 week window with the GoFundMe
  dependency flagged as a known blocker (timeline ask), the $4,200 fixed bid with
  a 40/40/20 milestone split (fixed-price ask), and a tight proof-points close.
  No em dashes or en dashes (verified via grep, zero matches).
- `proposal/one-pager.html` — Self-contained dark civic-tech HTML page (Newsreader
  display serif + Inter body, self-hostable Google Fonts, teal/gold accents, no
  partisan color coding). Sections: hero with live-demo CTA, the 10 sections
  listed in spec order, a LIVE/IN-DEVELOPMENT status-pill demonstration, the
  three coded data visualizations with inline SVG thumbnails, a full requirements
  traceability table, the 3-milestone timeline, the $4,200 price box, proof
  points, and a closing CTA linking both the demo and the work-samples route.
  Nonpartisan disclaimer footer included. No em/en dashes (verified).
- `proposal/make_deck.py` — python-pptx generator script (kept alongside the
  output per the existing repo convention, e.g. `edtech-school-connect-web-portal/make_deck.py`).
  Produces a 9-slide 16:9 deck in the same dark/teal/gold palette: title, the
  10-section spec list, the three data visualizations, the email-capture backend
  proof, requirements traceability, timeline/milestones, pricing, about Michael,
  and a closing CTA slide with the nonpartisan disclaimer. No em/en dashes.
- `proposal/deck.pptx` — Generated by running `make_deck.py` (ran successfully,
  `python3 make_deck.py`, 9 slides, ~44 KB).

## Links embedded (consistent across all three deliverables)

- Live demo: `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/`
- Portfolio / work-sample route: `https://michaelwegter.com/work-samples/civicq`
- Methodology page referenced: `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/methodology.html`

## Four to-apply asks, explicitly answered

1. **Portfolio** — live demo link is the first line of the cover letter and the
   hero CTA of both the one-pager and the deck.
2. **Timeline estimate** — concrete 3-milestone plan (week 1 / week 2 / weeks 3-4)
   inside the client's 2-4 week window, GoFundMe dependency flagged as a known
   external blocker, carried verbatim from `plan.md` section 8.
3. **Approach to the three custom graphics** — stated plainly in all three
   deliverables: Michael codes all three himself (SVG, no library, no designer
   assets), proven live in the demo.
4. **Fixed price bid** — $4,200, within the $3,500-$5,000 range, 40/40/20
   milestone split, matches `plan.md`'s recommendation.

## Requirements traceability

Every hard requirement from `intake.out` / `plan.md` (10 sections + sticky nav,
/methodology page, dark-mode system note, responsive 390/1440, Lighthouse 85+
mobile, all 3 data visualizations, email capture + CSV export, analytics,
WCAG 2.1 AA, GoFundMe CTA, US-based) is mapped explicitly in the one-pager's
requirements table and the deck's traceability slide, each tied to live,
verified evidence from `deploy-test.out` (all checks passed, VERDICT: pass).

## Writing rules compliance

- No em dashes, no en dashes anywhere across `cover-letter.md`, `one-pager.html`,
  `make_deck.py` (verified by grep against the em-dash/en-dash characters; zero
  matches in all three files).
- Cover letter follows Michael's voice shape from `reference/brand-voice.md`:
  hook, demo as differentiator, build approach, proof points, warm low-pressure
  close, signed "Michael."
- Nonpartisan tone maintained throughout: no red/blue color coding, no
  editorializing, "no spin, just the record" framing echoed, disclaimer line
  included on the one-pager and the deck's closing slide matching the posting's
  own disclaimer.

Ready for the evaluator phase.
